this is very case sensitive in words return all words having khan
db.students.find({name:{$regex:"khan"}})

to remove case sesitive
db.students.find({name:{$regex:/khan/}})

students whose name starts with m
 db.students.find({name:{$regex:"^m"}})

 students whose name ends with u
 db.students.find({name:{$regex:"u$"}})

 expression operator to compare diff
  db.students.find({$expr:{$gt:{"$spent","$budget"}}})

  mod operator is 
   db.students.find({age:{$mod:[5,0]}});
   divide every document age value by 5 and whose rem is 0 return those document
